headlines.description: — Evan Mobley had 26 points and the Cleveland Cavaliers scored 35 points off Charlotte turnovers to beat the Hornets for the second time in three days, 120-104 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavs defeat sloppy Hornets again without Mitchell, Allen

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 36 points, and the Washington Wizards snapped their three-game losing streak with a 117-97 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards snap 3-game skid with 117-97 rout of Pistons

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet scored 36 points, O.G. Anunoby had 24 and the Toronto Raptors used a franchise-record, 49-point first quarter to beat Denver 125-110 on Tuesday, handing the slumping Nuggets their season-high fourth straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet has 36, Raptors hand Nuggets 4th straight loss

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis' dominance inside and Malik Beasley's blazing start from behind the 3-point arc all but put away the Pelicans before halftime in a game that could prove pivotal in the Western Conference playoff picture.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis, Lakers lead by 35 at half, beat Pelicans 123-108

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 35 points, Josh Giddey had 15 points, 13 rebounds and 10 assists, and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Brooklyn Nets 121-107 on Tuesday night for their sixth win in seven games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder use big third quarter to rally past Nets, 121-107

events.name: Orlando Magic at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jeremy Sochan had 29 points and 11 rebounds and the San Antonio Spurs had a franchise-high 22 3-pointers and season-high 39 assists in a 132-114 win over the Orlando Magic on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sochan's double-double leads Spurs past Magic 132-114

headlines.description: — The Milwaukee Bucks walked into one of the toughest places to play in the NBA, snatched the lead from the Phoenix Suns midway through the fourth quarter and then closed with a flourish to earn a 116-104 victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks clinch playoff spot, top Suns 116-104 for 50th win

events.name: New York Knicks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Immanuel Quickley had 26 points and 10 rebounds, and the New York Knicks mounted a rally in the third quarter to beat the Portland Trail Blazers 123-107 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Quickley leads rally and Knicks beat Trail Blazers 123-107
